3003d9ea-08f1-4039-8643-5e496c016f0b.title: The Great War
3003d9ea-08f1-4039-8643-5e496c016f0b.description: Unlocks: Great War Infantry, Gunner,  Artillery, Ship

81e430d1-2d10-425d-80a0-5c05cd433b95.title: Trench Shotgun
81e430d1-2d10-425d-80a0-5c05cd433b95.description: The introduction of powerful pump-action shotguns provides a devastating tool for clearing enemy trenches in brutal close-quarters combat.

8844bcce-a6d4-449c-910b-e23c7ea13205.title: Early trenches
8844bcce-a6d4-449c-910b-e23c7ea13205.description: The first complex networks of trenches are dug, defining the static nature of the Western Front and changing the face of warfare forever.

a33f0925-3dbc-40ea-943b-7b293a3d0be6.title: Trench Warfare
a33f0925-3dbc-40ea-943b-7b293a3d0be6.description: Armies adapt to the stalemate by developing specialized tactics and equipment for trench assaults, including grenades, clubs, and stormtrooper units.

7f2e8807-18cf-4a17-aac2-efd4c6b405ad.title: Advanced Trenches
7f2e8807-18cf-4a17-aac2-efd4c6b405ad.description: Trenches evolve into multi-layered defensive systems with deep dugouts, concrete bunkers, and interlocking fields of fire, making them incredibly difficult to assault.

52458ec9-536e-4abd-8b92-f22187b2882b.title: 1907 Artillery
52458ec9-536e-4abd-8b92-f22187b2882b.description: Modern quick-firing field guns are adopted, capable of providing accurate and sustained fire support for infantry operations.

aba9ce8e-9e06-4d48-953a-493a2ef0b899.title: Assault Artillery Doctrine
aba9ce8e-9e06-4d48-953a-493a2ef0b899.description: A focus on close-range, direct fire support for infantry assaults, using specialized troops and equipment to break through fortified lines.

f5d5f3f5-9e5b-4d7b-a124-9313677fbb63.title: 1916 Artillery
f5d5f3f5-9e5b-4d7b-a124-9313677fbb63.description: The concept of the 'creeping barrage' is perfected, with artillery fire moving just ahead of advancing troops to suppress enemy defenders.

e47a2ab5-284f-4b4e-9ff0-09119e8804ad.title: 1914 Artillery
e47a2ab5-284f-4b4e-9ff0-09119e8804ad.description: At the outbreak of war, massive railway guns and heavy howitzers are mobilized to smash enemy fortifications from afar.

fdc98a8a-c8ca-40d5-ab2f-48b723a34f51.title: Long Range
fdc98a8a-c8ca-40d5-ab2f-48b723a34f51.description: Improvements in gun design and propellant chemistry allow artillery to strike targets deeper behind enemy lines, disrupting logistics and command.

22f997d8-ab30-4d41-9d7b-bfbafc864839.title: Bomber Planes
22f997d8-ab30-4d41-9d7b-bfbafc864839.description: Early bombers are developed to carry small payloads, capable of striking strategic targets like railyards and factories far behind the front lines.

e7467ad3-a44a-48b2-9f59-8f3c8814874a.title: Fighter planes
e7467ad3-a44a-48b2-9f59-8f3c8814874a.description: The skies become a new battlefield as nimble fighter aircraft, armed with machine guns, are developed to shoot down enemy reconnaissance planes and bombers.

7faa722a-de69-4220-86e1-bd517b5e9bf2.title: Warplanes
7faa722a-de69-4220-86e1-bd517b5e9bf2.description: Aircraft are militarized for the first time, initially for reconnaissance, but quickly adapted for combat roles.

39c1a505-75e4-4941-ad7d-7492feac48f4.title: Early Planes
39c1a505-75e4-4941-ad7d-7492feac48f4.description: The fragile wood and fabric aircraft of the pre-war era take to the skies, primarily used to observe enemy moveme

541fb884-df2b-40ba-b783-e4318cac8179.title: Heavy Machinegun Nest
541fb884-df2b-40ba-b783-e4318cac8179.description: Strategically placed, well-protected machine gun nests can halt entire divisions, becoming the cornerstone of trench defense.

ec11cee2-0de3-4bf9-9959-2da89d100b2e.title: Bigger Payload
ec11cee2-0de3-4bf9-9959-2da89d100b2e.description: Bomber designs are improved to carry heavier and more numerous bombs, increasing their destructive potential against ground targets.

cbbd88f4-031d-45b4-b281-8d16553b6595.title: Machines of War
cbbd88f4-031d-45b4-b281-8d16553b6595.description: The industrial might of nations is fully harnessed, leading to the development of armored vehicles and other mechanical marvels of destruction.

26d7c1b2-86f9-4236-8f79-0cd0b6f220c5.title: 1910 Early Mech
26d7c1b2-86f9-4236-8f79-0cd0b6f220c5.description: Experimental walking machines, inspired by early agricultural tractors, are conceptualized as a way to cross the shell-torn No Man's Land.

ac8fe825-c8a9-4d34-abbd-b5f887e19ced.title: 1918 Mech
ac8fe825-c8a9-4d34-abbd-b5f887e19ced.description: Late-war mechs become formidable fighting machines, combining mobility, armor, and firepower that foreshadow the future of armored warfare.

7e8bde9a-3f51-44c2-baba-dc9bb19ba1bc.title: 1916 Mech
7e8bde9a-3f51-44c2-baba-dc9bb19ba1bc.description: Battlefield experience refines mech design, leading to better-armored and more reliably armed walkers capable of supporting infantry assaults.

1691fba6-d001-48a1-a30f-98e4c0691707.title: 1914 Mech
1691fba6-d001-48a1-a30f-98e4c0691707.description: With the war's outbreak, early mech prototypes are rushed into development, focusing on armor and the ability to traverse trenches.

20a95e15-1c17-4e91-8b7c-075f2bcf0da2.title: Artillery Mech 1919
20a95e15-1c17-4e91-8b7c-075f2bcf0da2.description: Post-war mech designs incorporate dedicated, long-range artillery platforms, capable of keeping pace with mechanized advances.

bd5da343-37db-4b28-b5eb-2cb7d100e0b8.title: Artillery Mech 1917
bd5da343-37db-4b28-b5eb-2cb7d100e0b8.description: Improved designs allow for heavier cannons to be mounted on mechs, providing direct fire support against enemy bunkers and strongpoints.

28d79a04-37f2-43e5-af59-8a81ac8fc330.title: Artillery Mech 1915
28d79a04-37f2-43e5-af59-8a81ac8fc330.description: The first attempts are made to mount light artillery pieces on walking platforms, creating a mobile fire support unit.

def7c51a-520d-4b75-af6e-9c27b2e3e851.title: L. Mech 1917
def7c51a-520d-4b75-af6e-9c27b2e3e851.description: Late-war light mechs are faster and more agile, used for flanking maneuvers and harassing enemy supply lines.

86167a1b-f08d-4f94-90fc-71445f0b9534.title: L. mech 1915
86167a1b-f08d-4f94-90fc-71445f0b9534.description: The need for fast-moving units to exploit breakthroughs leads to the development of the first light mechs, armed with machine guns.

0109ad8a-a34e-46ae-a898-3681a4d6e2a5.title: L. Mech 1912
0109ad8a-a34e-46ae-a898-3681a4d6e2a5.description: Early concepts for light, fast-moving walking machines are explored for cavalry and reconnaissance roles.

4d64dd11-91e4-4919-83c8-8d5502f8c4d1.title: Interwar Period
4d64dd11-91e4-4919-83c8-8d5502f8c4d1.description: The Great War is over, but the technological race continues. Nations refine the lessons learned, preparing for the next inevitable conflict.

14f5fe8c-4edd-4d29-ab1f-b0072f69ed5b.title: 1900 Ship
14f5fe8c-4edd-4d29-ab1f-b0072f69ed5b.description: The pre-dreadnought era of battleships, with their mixed-caliber main guns, still rules the waves.

e1eba71c-f574-4a74-aa24-6e2e2c032ed7.title: 1910 Ship
e1eba71c-f574-4a74-aa24-6e2e2c032ed7.description: The commissioning of HMS Dreadnought revolutionizes naval warfare, introducing the 'all-big-gun' battleship design that all major powers rush to copy.

9bc10601-67d5-4a1c-a480-c78b774eeef6.title: 1914 Ship
9bc10601-67d5-4a1c-a480-c78b774eeef6.description: Navies enter the war with fleets of powerful dreadnoughts and battlecruisers, prepared for a decisive clash for control of the seas.

ede3ac3c-a0e2-41dd-92c0-72c1ce547880.title: 1916 Ship
ede3ac3c-a0e2-41dd-92c0-72c1ce547880.description: The Battle of Jutland demonstrates the power and vulnerability of modern warships, leading to improvements in armor, fire control, and damage control.

69f7b312-0cb4-4dae-a80c-6cbcb0401c15.title: 1918 Ship
69f7b312-0cb4-4dae-a80c-6cbcb0401c15.description: Late-war ship designs incorporate advanced features like anti-aircraft guns and improved submarine detection, adapting to new threats.

3b5248cb-6b17-4834-89a8-a9a26c355a86.title: 1907 BattleShip
3b5248cb-6b17-4834-89a8-a9a26c355a86.description: The first dreadnoughts are launched, their uniform main batteries making every previous battleship obsolete overnight.

3c771620-19a4-4e9e-acfd-65217f33d56a.title: 1916 Battleship
3c771620-19a4-4e9e-acfd-65217f33d56a.description: Lessons from early naval battles lead to enhanced deck armor to protect against plunging fire and better internal subdivision to resist torpedo damage.

9033b2f9-ced7-4afd-8587-6b14b4946855.title: 1919 BattleShip
9033b2f9-ced7-4afd-8587-6b14b4946855.description: The war's end sees the pinnacle of dreadnought design, massive ships with unprecedented firepower and protection.

4229272d-baa0-46c5-a381-23f0d5ca4fc0.title: 1912 Battleship
4229272d-baa0-46c5-a381-23f0d5ca4fc0.description: Super-dreadnoughts are built, featuring larger guns, thicker armor, and more powerful turbine engines.

e9becbc5-ed61-4dfa-9dce-9e1d34e8b8c6.title: 1914 Submarine
e9becbc5-ed61-4dfa-9dce-9e1d34e8b8c6.description: Submarines become a serious threat, capable of long-range patrols and sinking merchant ships and warships with deadly torpedoes.

3f70fa16-622c-476c-90b1-6f5cc7739671.title: 1907 Submarine
3f70fa16-622c-476c-90b1-6f5cc7739671.description: Early submarines are primarily coastal defense vessels, limited by unreliable engines and short range.

97d28cfc-44dc-483d-9993-601b99245165.title: 1917 Submarine
97d28cfc-44dc-483d-9993-601b99245165.description: The implementation of unrestricted submarine warfare by Germany brings the U-boat to the forefront of the naval conflict, nearly starving Britain into submission.

339b0c9d-25a0-4cda-98e3-3336e013a778.title: 1919 Submarine
339b0c9d-25a0-4cda-98e3-3336e013a778.description: Post-war submarines are larger, faster, and have much longer range, evolving into true fleet boats.

d5d28ff4-349d-4f84-86c6-ce67640ac49a.title: Early Aircraft Carrier
d5d28ff4-349d-4f84-86c6-ce67640ac49a.description: The first experiments are conducted in launching and recovering aircraft from modified ship decks, hinting at a future shift in naval power.

b5e4da84-a3a8-40b9-b0e4-f6aa937881a4.title: 1919 Trucks
b5e4da84-a3a8-40b9-b0e4-f6aa937881a4.description: The war solidifies the role of the truck as the backbone of military logistics, with designs that would be used for decades.

79502d92-8669-4e68-a287-21454c2fd967.title: 1917 Trucks
79502d92-8669-4e68-a287-21454c2fd967.description: Mass production of robust and reliable military trucks allows for unprecedented logistical capacity, keeping the massive armies supplied.

4cdd9f79-0c57-4e57-a2dd-06c555fa8c33.title: Ancient Era
4cdd9f79-0c57-4e57-a2dd-06c555fa8c33.description: All Clubman upgrade to Hoplite for free.

e935d76b-10b1-4509-a135-e2eec0f8f9e5.title: Shoping Outposts
e935d76b-10b1-4509-a135-e2eec0f8f9e5.description: Traders begin to build trading outposts in other cities
